{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nAttestation manifests must carry the rebar gate-code version+SHA for audit\nprovenance (epic jira-reb-596). This story adds the value where it is signed and\nthe parser to read it back — the core of the feature, with no build or display\nsurface yet.\n\n## What\n\n- Add a gate-code SHA/version resolver in `src/rebar/signing.py` (co-located with\n  and reusing the `head_sha()` idiom, line 337 — a `git -C … rev-parse` subprocess;\n  do NOT invent a new git wrapper). It returns `\"<version> (<short-sha>[-dirty])\"`,\n  or just `\"<version>\"` when no SHA is resolvable:\n  - Version: `rebar.__version__`.\n  - SHA: `git -C <dir of rebar.__file__> rev-parse --short HEAD` — the **rebar\n    source (gate code)** dir, NOT the target repo. Resolution is **live-git-first,\n    omit-last** (build-baked fallback = story 2).\n  - `-dirty` rule: append `-dirty` iff `git -C <dir of rebar.__file__> status\n    --porcelain` is non-empty (any staged / modified-tracked / untracked change in\n    the rebar source tree).\n  - Any git failure -> omit the SHA (version only) and emit a debug log\n    (silent-failure guard).\n- Append one `rebar-version:` line to BOTH manifests:\n  - `build_manifest` — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (plan-review).\n  - `_verdict_manifest` — `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py:282`\n    (completion-verifier).\n- Add `manifest_rebar_version(manifest)` in `attest.py` (mirroring\n  `manifest_regver`) returning the stamp, or `None` for pre-stamp manifests.\n- `compute_validity` stays untouched and must never read the stamp.\n\n## Scope\n\nSigning + parsing only. Build-time baking = story 2; `show`/`verify_signature`\nsurfacing = story 3.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `build_manifest` and `_verdict_manifest` both emit a `rebar-version:` line.\n- [ ] Resolver returns the live-git short SHA with a `-dirty` suffix per the rule when the rebar source checkout is dirty.\n- [ ] Resolver omits the SHA (version-only string) and emits a debug log on git failure / non-git install.\n- [ ] `manifest_rebar_version()` round-trips the stamp and returns `None` for a pre-stamp manifest.\n- [ ] `compute_validity` behavior is byte-for-byte unchanged; a pre-stamp manifest still validates.\n- [ ] Existing tests asserting on `build_manifest` / `_verdict_manifest` output are updated for the new line.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: both manifests carry the line; live-checkout `-dirty` resolution; git-absent omit; parser round-trip; pre-stamp `None`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783125238858401001,"uuid":"65aeeec8-430a-4e70-a191-891c22530531"}